$ Oracle: V$SYSTEM_EVENT
@ v$system_event

`v$system_event` summarizes the total wait times since the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance
→ development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/startup-shutdown[started up], broken up
for each → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/event_name#ora-interesting-event-names[event].

code {
select
   sev.event,
   sev.total_timeouts,
   total_timeouts_fg,
   round(sev.time_waited_micro_fg / 1000 / 1000 / 24 / 60 / 60, 1) waited_hrs_fg,
   round(sev.time_waited_micro    / 1000 / 1000 / 24 / 60 / 60, 1) waited_hrs,
-- round(sev.time_waited          / 100         / 24 / 60 / 60, 1) waited_hrs,
-- round(sev.time_waited_fg       / 100         / 24 / 60 / 60, 1) waited_fg_hrs,
   round(sev.average_wait_fg      / 100         / 24 / 60 / 60, 1) avg_wait_fg_hrs,
   round(sev.average_wait         / 100         / 24 / 60 / 60, 1) avg_wait_hrs,
   sev.total_waits,
   sev.total_waits_fg,
   sev.wait_class
from
   v$system_event  sev
where
   sev.wait_class not in ('Idle')
order by
   sev.time_waited_micro_fg desc;
code }

sa:

  The → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views[Oracle Dynamic Performance Views]
    • → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/session/event[`v$session_vent`]
    • → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/event_name[`v$event_name`]
    • → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/enqueue_stat[`v$enqueue_stat`]

